# LLM Execution Protocol (Antigravity)

This protocol applies to all coding tasks managed by Antigravity agents.

## Default Mode: STRICT

### Classification
Every task must be classified before execution:
- Task type: BUG_FIX | FEATURE | REFACTOR | EXPLORATION
- Risk level: LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH
- Mode: STRICT | FAST | DEBUG

### Protocol (6 Stages)
1. Assumptions — list all, verify uncertain ones
2. Interpretations — ≥2 alternatives, surface differences
3. Decision — choose with justification, reject alternatives
4. Plan — ordered steps, each with verification criterion
5. Implementation — one step at a time, no side effects
6. Verification — tests, linters, unrelated changes check

### Enforcement
- R1: Only task-related lines changed
- R2: No unused abstractions
- R3: Match existing code style
- R5: Tests must pass before reporting done
- R6: >50 line diffs require line-by-line justification
- R8: All changes must be revertible

### Self-Evaluation
Post-task: score correctness (3x), minimality (2x), assumption accuracy (2x), process compliance (2x), verification (1x). Fail if weighted < 7 or any < 4.
